I"[<p>A major ethical challenge for our times.  There can be little doubt that surveillance is a major ethical challenge for our times, especially with the onset of the internet.  Much of the current concern focuses on the potential of governments to peruse the contents of emails from individuals, most often under the guise of protecting national security.  Email communication is certainly convenient for individuals, and has now all but replaced traditional postal communication, but the ease by which it is possible to intercept emails raises important questions of privacy and democratic rights.</p>
